column5: Every year these suckers come into shore around the last week of May. Today was not the best for pics(overcast & a slight chop)but I gave it my best effort. As you can see they are right under my dock & boatlift.      Lots of splashing along the shoreline,but every time I tried to catch the action they must have sensed  my presence & headed to deeper water.
Awesome, thanks for sharing! Man, thats some clear water!!!
